<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML+RDFa 1.0//EN" "http://www.w3.org/MarkUp/DTD/xhtml-rdfa-1.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
      xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
      xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
      xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
      metal:use-macro="engine_template/macros/page"
      i18n:domain="cc_org">

<head>
  <title metal:fill-slot="title">Choose a License</title>

  <metal:headers fill-slot="headers">

    <script type="text/javascript"
            src="http://yui.yahooapis.com/2.6.0/build/container/container-min.js">
    </script> 

    <script tal:attributes="src python:request.staticdirect('/includes/help.js')"
            type="text/javascript">
    </script>
  </metal:headers>
</head>

<body>
  <metal:title metal:fill-slot="page-header-title"
               i18n:translate="license.License_Your_Work">
    License Your Work
  </metal:title>
    
  <div metal:fill-slot="body">


    <p i18n:translate="license.what">
      With a Creative Commons license, <strong>you keep your
      copyright</strong> but allow people
      to <a href="/learn/licenses/fullrights">copy and distribute your
      work</a> provided they <a href="#" class="helpLink"
      id="give_you_credit">give you credit</a> &mdash; and only on the
      conditions you specify here. For those new to Creative Commons
      licensing, we've prepared <a href="/about/think">a list of
      things to think about</a>. If you want to offer your work with
      no conditions attached, or you want to mark a work that is
      already free of known copyright restrictions and in the public
      domain, choose one of our <a href="/publicdomain/">public domain
      tools</a>.
    </p> 

     <p i18n:translate="license.explain">
       When you choose a <a href="http://creativecommons.org/about/licenses">license</a>, 
       we provide you with HTML you can use to add the
       license information to your site and information on how to select a license on
       one of several free hosting services that have incorporated Creative Commons. 
       This is not a registration and we do not retain a record of your selection.
    </p>

    <div id="help_give_you_credit" class="help_panel">
      <div class="hd" i18n:translate="char.by_title">Attribution</div>
      <div class="bd" i18n:translate="char.by_description">
        You must attribute the work in the manner specified by the author or licensor.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="licensebox">
      <form action="./results-one" method="get" >
        <div>
          <input type="hidden"  name="q_1" value="2" id="question_1-2"
                 checked="checked" /> 
          <input type="hidden" name="q_1" value="1" id="question_1-1" />
        </div>    

        <p>
          <strong i18n:translate="api.commercial">
            Allow commercial uses of your work?
          </strong>
        </p>
        <ul class="choices">
          <li>
            <input type="radio" checked="checked"
                   name="field_commercial" value="y" id="question_2-3"/>
            <label for="question_2-3"
                   i18n:translate="util.Yes">Yes</label> 
            <a href="" id="commercial" class="helpLink">
              <img src="images/information.png"
                   tal:attributes="src python:request.staticdirect('images/information.png')"
                   i18n:attributes="alt" alt="Information"/>
            </a>
          </li>

          <li>
            <input type="radio"  
                   name="field_commercial" value="n" id="question_2-4"/>
            <label for="question_2-4"
                   i18n:translate="util.No">No</label>
            <a href="" id="noncommercial" class="helpLink">
              <img src="images/information.png"
                   tal:attributes="src python:request.staticdirect('images/information.png')"
                   i18n:attributes="alt" alt="Information"/>
            </a>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          <strong i18n:translate="api.derivatives">
            Allow modifications of your work?
          </strong>
        </p>
                
        <ul class="choices">
          <li>
            <input type="radio" checked="checked" 
                   name="field_derivatives" value="y"
                   id="question_3-5" />  
            <label for="question_3-5" i18n:translate="util.Yes">Yes</label>
            <a href="" id="derivatives" class="helpLink">
              <img src="images/information.png"
                   tal:attributes="src python:request.staticdirect('images/information.png')"
                   i18n:attributes="alt" alt="Information" />
            </a>
          </li>
            
          <li>
            <input type="radio" name="field_derivatives" value="sa" 
                   id="question_3-6" /> 
            <label for="question_3-6">
              <span i18n:translate="">Yes, as long as others share alike</span>
              <a href="" class="helpLink" id="sharealike">
                <img src="images/information.png"
                     tal:attributes="src python:request.staticdirect('images/information.png')"
                     i18n:attributes="alt" alt="Information" />
              </a>
            </label>
          </li>

          <li>
            <input type="radio"  name="field_derivatives" value="n" 
                   id="question_3-7" /> 
            <label for="question_3-7" i18n:translate="util.No">No</label>
            <a href="" id="noderivatives" class="helpLink">
              <img src="images/information.png"
                   tal:attributes="src python:request.staticdirect('images/information.png')"
                   i18n:attributes="alt" alt="Information" />
            </a>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          <span tal:omit-tag="" i18n:translate="license.jurisdiction_question">
            Jurisdiction of your license
          </span> 
          <a href="" class="helpLink" id="jurisdiction">
            <img src="images/information.png"
                 tal:attributes="src python:request.staticdirect('images/information.png')"
                 i18n:attributes="alt" alt="Information" />
          </a>
          <br />

          <select name="field_jurisdiction" tal:condition="not: requested_jurisdiction">
            <option value=""  
                    i18n:translate="util.International" selected="selected">
              International
            </option> 

            <span tal:omit-tag=""
                  tal:repeat="j jurisdictions_names">
              <option value=""
                      tal:attributes="value python: j[0];">
                <span tal:content="python: j[1]"
                      tal:omit-tag=""
                      i18n:translate="" />
              </option>
            </span>
          </select>

          <select name="field_jurisdiction" tal:condition="requested_jurisdiction">
            <option value="" i18n:translate="util.International">
              International
            </option> 

            <span tal:omit-tag=""
                  tal:repeat="j jurisdictions_names">
              <option value="" selected="selected"
                      tal:condition="python: j[0] == requested_jurisdiction"
                      tal:attributes="value python: j[0];">
                <span tal:content="python: j[1]"
                      tal:omit-tag=""
                      i18n:translate="" />
              </option>
              <option value=""
                      tal:condition="python: j[0] != requested_jurisdiction"
                      tal:attributes="value python: j[0];">
                <span tal:content="python: j[1]"
                      tal:omit-tag=""
                      i18n:translate="" />
              </option>
            </span>
          </select>
        </p>

        <div metal:use-macro="metadata_template/macros/more-metadata" />

        <div>
          <input type="hidden" name="lang" value="en"
                 tal:attributes="value target_lang" /> 
          <input type="hidden" name="n_questions" value="3" />
        </div>
    
        <div>
          <p> 
            <input type="submit" class="submit"
                   i18n:attributes="value license.Select_a_License;" 
                   value="Select a License" />
          </p>    
        </div>
      </form>
    </div>
    <br />

    <div metal:use-macro="support_template/macros/engine_languages"></div>
    
    <div id="help_jurisdiction">
      <div class="hd">
        <span i18n:translate="util.Jurisdiction">Jurisdiction</span>
      </div>
      <div class="bd">
        <p i18n:translate="license.jurisdiction_help">
          Use the option "International" if you desire a license using language
          and terminology from international treaties.  If the licenses have
          been ported to your jurisdiction and you feel that your jurisdiction's
          ported licenses account for some aspect of local legislation that the
          international licenses do not, then you may want to consider <a href="http://wiki.creativecommons.org/Frequently_Asked_Questions#Should_I_choose_an_international_license_or_a_ported_license.3F">which
            license is better suited for your needs</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="help_commercial">
      <div class="hd">
        <span i18n:translate="">Commercial Use</span>
      </div>
      <div class="bd">
        <p i18n:translate="license.help.commercial">
          The licensor permits others to copy, distribute, display, and
          perform the work, including for commercial purposes.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
                        
    <div id="help_noncommercial">
      <div class="hd">
        <span i18n:translate="licenses.pretty_nc">Noncommercial</span>
      </div>
      <div class="bd">
        <p i18n:translate="license.help.noncommercial">
          The licensor permits others to copy, distribute, display,
          and perform the work for non-commercial purposes only.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
                        
    <div id="help_derivatives">
      <div class="hd">
        <span i18n:translate="">Allow Derivative Works</span>
      </div>
      <div class="bd">
        <p i18n:translate="license.help.derivatives">
          The licensor permits others to copy, distribute, display
          and perform the work, as well as make derivative works
          based on it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div id="help_noderivatives">
      <div class="hd">
        <span i18n:translate="char.nd_title">No Derivative Works</span>
      </div>
      <div class="bd">
        <p i18n:translate="char.nd_description">
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div id="help_sharealike">
      <div class="hd">
        <span i18n:translate="char.sa_title">Share-Alike</span>
      </div>
      <div class="bd">
        <p i18n:translate="char.sa_description">
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
